          "type": "plan",
          "text": "# Animated Fizzy CLI Banner\n\n## Context\n\nThe Fizzy CLI has a braille-art banner (5 popsicles + \"FIZZY\" text) with animated color reveal. Ported from Basecamp CLI's animation system, adapted for Fizzy's 5 multi-colored popsicles.\n\n## Logo Colors (from logo.png)\n\nFive popsicles, left to right:\n1. **Blue** `#3B82F6`\n2. **Magenta** `#EC4899`\n3. **Orange** `#F97316`\n4. **Lime** `#84CC16`\n5. **Cyan** `#06B6D4`\n\nDark-mode trail per popsicle: white flash вҶ’ light tint вҶ’ brand color (3 stages).\n\n## Banner Grid Zones\n\nThe braille banner is 80 columns wide, 12 rows:\n- **Cols 0-7** вҶ’ Zone 0 (Blue popsicle)\n- **Cols 8-12** вҶ’ Zone 1 (Magenta popsicle)\n- **Cols 13-16** вҶ’ Zone 2 (Orange popsicle)\n- **Cols 17-21** вҶ’ Zone 3 (Lime popsicle)\n- **Cols 22-25** вҶ’ Zone 4 (Cyan popsicle)\n- **Cols 26+** вҶ’ Zone 5 (FIZZY wordmark)\n\nOnly dense braille characters (3+ raised dots) are painted/colored. Sparse characters (0-2 dots) are background texture вҖ” rendered as blank in colored mode to eliminate speckling.\n\n## Architecture\n\n`internal/tui/` package. lipgloss v1.1.0, `go-isatty` for TTY detection, `charmbracelet/x/term` for terminal width.\n\n### Files\n\n**`internal/tui/banner.go`** вҖ” Banner constant, grid parsing, zone mapping, density filter, static render\n- `Banner` const вҖ” the braille art\n- `PopsicleColors [5]lipgloss.Color` вҖ” the 5 brand colors\n- `isDense(ch rune) bool` вҖ” braille chars with 3+ dots (visible shapes vs background texture)\n- `popsicleZone(col int) int` вҖ” column вҶ’ zone index\n- `bannerGrid() ([][]rune, int)` вҖ” parse banner into rune grid\n- `RenderBanner(w io.Writer) string` вҖ” writer-bound colored render (nil = plain text)\n- `rendererForWriter(w) *lipgloss.Renderer` вҖ” creates writer-bound lipgloss renderer\n- `bannerVisualRows(cols int) int` вҖ” accounts for soft-wrap in narrow terminals\n\n**`internal/tui/banner_anim.go`** вҖ” Animation engine\n- `AnimateBanner(w io.Writer)` вҖ” synchronous animation\n- `AnimateBannerAsync(w io.Writer) (io.Writer, func())` вҖ” async with AnimWriter\n- Two strategies via `FIZZY_ANIM` env var:\n  - **`pop`** (default) вҖ” popsicles pop up bottom-to-top, text sweeps left-to-right\n  - **`paint`** вҖ” popsicles paint top-to-bottom simultaneously with radial text unfurl\n- `AnimWriter` struct вҖ” mutex-protected writer tracking visual rows and column position\n- Per-zone trail styles via writer-bound renderer\n- `renderPaintFrame` / `renderPaintLine` вҖ” zone+age grouped styled runs\n- `bannerVisualRows` used for cursor-up (handles narrow terminal wrapping)\n\n**`internal/tui/banner_test.go`** вҖ” 24 tests covering zones, dimensions, density filter, render, non-TTY fallback, trace coverage, text ordering, visual line wrapping, AnimWriter tracking\n\n### Animation Strategies\n\n**`pop`** (default) вҖ” Popsicles pop up from bottom-to-top with stagger cascade, then FIZZY text sweeps left-to-right column-by-column.\n\n**`paint`** вҖ” Popsicles paint top-to-bottom with stagger cascade. FIZZY wordmark unfurls simultaneously via radial distance from top-left corner of text zone (quarter-ellipse wavefront). Text cell order scaled to `[0, maxPopsicleEnd]` so popsicles and text finish together.\n\n### Density Filter\n\n`isDense(ch)` uses `bits.OnesCount(ch - 0x2800) > 2` to separate shape characters (3+ dots) from background texture (0-2 dots). Applied in:\n- `renderBannerWith` вҖ” sparse chars replaced with blank braille\n- `renderPaintLine` вҖ” sparse chars treated as background\n- `traceWithOrder` вҖ” only dense chars enter the paint trace\n\n## Graceful Degradation\n\n- `FIZZY_ANIM=paint|pop` вҖ” select strategy (default: `pop`)\n- `FIZZY_ANIM=none` вҖ” static colored render, no animation\n- `NO_COLOR` set вҖ” static plain render (no ANSI)\n- Not a TTY вҖ” static plain render (no ANSI)\n- Machine output flags вҖ” suppressed entirely (existing behavior)\n\n## Status: Complete\n",
